<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Calron</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-27 15:41:30</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This is one of the best spells in the game.  You will use this to level 50.  Always cast on MOB first.  If you cast root on MOB it will over write this spell, so when it breaks root it will be full speed.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Montrovant</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-28 01:14:36</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This spell will also override a necro/SK's darkness line of spells. Make sure if you are in a group with a necro/SK that they know your snareing, so they won't waste mana on castng the darkness.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: anon</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-29 14:02:02</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Snare is a great spell.  I use it more than any other one spell I think.  But there are some times when root spells are a good idea, like when you want to make sure the NPC doesn't budge...in a dungeon where one step is the difference between living peacefully or a HUGE train killing you.  Be sure your group knows when you think root is a good spell to have instead of snare.  And be sure that one of you is the designated "rooter" so there aren't multiple spells cancelling each other.</font></td></tr></table>
